## Implementation Notes
- Use these font sizes and line heights for all headings, body text, captions, and overlines.
- Use responsive classes (e.g., Tailwind’s `text-4xl md:text-6xl`) to switch between mobile and desktop sizes.
- Set line heights using Tailwind’s `leading-` utilities or custom CSS if needed.
- If you have a specific font-family, set it globally in your CSS.
- Use semantic HTML tags (`h1`, `h2`, `p`, etc.) and apply these styles via classes.
